	<clause id="directory_and_file_structure" obligation="normative"><title>Directory and File Structure</title><clause id="directory_and_file_structure_introduction" obligation="normative">
	<title>Introduction</title>
	<p id="_cb8a441b-67a8-4ee3-9a51-e589e6b304c5">The scheme does not mandate the use of a particular directory or file structure. However, because the entire ENC data file is encrypted it is difficult to maintain some vital file associations, e.g. text and picture files with the relevant ENC cell file (base or update). The directory structure that has been adopted by existing Data Servers is given in an example below in <xref target="folder_definitions"/>. This structure enables text and picture files to be safely managed by maintaining a direct relationship between them and the corresponding ENC data file.</p>
	</clause>
	<clause id="s57_file_management" obligation="normative">
(XML Line 002122): Hanging paragraph in clause
