	<clause id="enc_cell_permit_installation" obligation="normative"><title>ENC Cell Permit Installation</title><p id="_6f7551da-b7ec-4811-a08e-3565f221cf89">New Cell permits are delivered to a Data Client’s system in a file named PERMIT.TXT. The structure and format of this file are given in <xref target="the_cell_permit"/>. The Data Clients system must be able to read in this file and perform a number of checks. Each cell permit record contains a Data Server ID that enables OEMs to manage permits and data in a multi supplier environment. The following sections outline how this file must be managed and the checks that must be carried out when installing a new permit file.</p>
	<clause id="check_for_a_cell_permit" obligation="normative"><title>Check for a Cell Permit</title><p id="_910899d4-e3e6-48ac-8ac0-c1b0d027341c">The Data Client system must first check that a valid cell permit is available to install. A facility should be available for Data Clients to browse to a specific location on the system where the PERMIT.TXT file is available to install. If any text file other than one named PERMIT.TXT file is selected the system should return a warning as follows:</p>
	<quote id="_3d65bf49-2736-4efb-a8c6-c41cb6014f31">
	<p id="_bd279e93-0589-4c5e-ab56-4d01b91914a2">
	<strong>
